    {
      "id": "67af03fe-296c-43b6-9c7e-ca744f74b6e7",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors considered 141 students and, for those, relied on 3 distinct data sources: Student Record System, LMS and survey data. Then, the authors attempt 3 base learners and a stack of different base learners. Ensembles trained with data from multiple data sources outperforms the remaining options. Models trained use accuracy. Also, no mention of a specific moment of prediction.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "67af03fe-296c-43b6-9c7e-ca744f74b6e7",
